{
  "doc_id": "43688",
  "text": "In this study, we tested the solubility of DCBNT in 12 commonly used solvents: water (H 2 O), dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO), N,N-diethylformamide (DEF), N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF), 1,4-butyrolactone (BL), methanol, ethanol, acetone, trichloromethane, dioxane, acetonitrile and ethyl acetate, and five binary solvents (volume ratio = 1 : 1), at atmospheric pressure using a polythermal method [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] with the CrystalSCAN system. The experimental solubility data were correlated by the modified Apelblat model, the Yaws model and the polynomial model. The thermodynamic magnitudes, such as the dissolution enthalpy, dissolution entropy and molar Gibbs free energy, were then obtained from the solubility data. The driving force of the process was determined by enthalpy-entropy compensation analysis [CITATION_3] .",
